HARARE, Zimbabwe, June 1, 2020/APO Group/ --
                                                        
                            Highlights of the Situation Report




	Four (4) cases tested positive for COVID-19. These are returnees from Mozambique (1) and South Africa (3) who are all isolated.
	214 RDT screening tests and 566 PCR diagnostic tests were done. The cumulative number of tests done to date is 45395 (27323 RDT and 18072 PCR).
	To date the total number of confirmed cases is 178; recovered 29, active cases 145 and 4 deaths, since the onset of the outbreak on 20 March 2020.





	
		
			
			
